  "texts": [
    "A digital signature system consists of four symbols and three core components, totaling seven parts.",
    "For the four symbols, k ∈ N is the security parameter of whole DSS, and M, S, H stand for message space, signature space and key space respectively.",
    "The core component of DSS is denoted as π = (Gen, Sign, Vrfy) where the the Gen and Sign are PPT (probabilistic polynomial time) algorithms, and Vrfy algorithm is deterministic.",
    "For the process of a DSS:",
    "• (pk, sk) ← Gen(1 k) where the pk, sk represent the public key and secret key respectively."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}